Kaleidoscope Music Therapy was founded by Sarah Kennedy, Jazz Vocalist, Songwriter and Certified Music Therapist. The concept behind Kaleidoscope Music Therapy (KMT) is that music is a powerful tool for examining and changing our perspectives. When you turn a kaleidoscope towards the sun and adjust the view, you inevitably discover new and beautiful colours. In much the same way, music can reveal new and beautiful ways to relate to life. If you are seeking mental health support, music therapy could be an effective approach for you.

Kaleidoscope Music Therapy was founded by Sarah Kennedy, Jazz Vocalist, Songwriter and Certified Music Therapist. The concept behind Kaleidoscope Music Therapy (KMT) is that music is a powerful tool for examining and changing our perspectives. When you turn a kaleidoscope towards the sun and adjust the view, you inevitably discover new and beautiful colours. In much the same way, music can reveal new and beautiful ways to relate to life. If you are seeking mental health support, music therapy could be an effective approach for you.

KMT serves clients in-person in Montreal and remotely anywhere within Canada. At KMT your life experiences will be validated and you will be supported and empowered to discover a more harmonious way of being.

Sarah Kennedy completed a Masters in Creative Arts Therapies from Concordia University in Montreal. She is passionate about supporting those experiencing grief and loss, depression, anxiety, chronic pain, serious illness, relationship distress and life transitions. She has significant professional and lived experience in these areas.
